Description: Fragment of a model discoid mace-head made of unfired Nile clay, preserving about two-thirds of the object.
Curator's comments: Published: E. R. Ayrton & W. L. S. Loat, 'Pre-dynastic cemetery at El Mahasna' (London, 1911), 21. A real stone mace of the same shape was found in the same tomb (see EA 49003)
